PrecisSetting apart, for the use and benefit of the PIAPOT BAND, of some 129.50 hectares (320 acres) of land, mines and minerals, situated near the Village of Dummer, in the Rural Municipality of Elmsthorpe No. 100, approximately 10 kilometres from the village of Truax, Saskatchewan, as an addition to Piapot Indian Reserve No. 75.
